## Summary

`openclaw status --deep` falsely reports `WARN Gateway HTTP APIs are reachable without auth` and `gateway.auth.mode="none"` when the gateway auth token is supplied via a secret reference instead of inline plaintext. The JSON status path (`status --deep --json`) and the dedicated `security audit --deep --json` both correctly report no auth warning.

## Root Cause

`STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS` in `src/cli/command-secret-targets.ts` listed only memory search API key paths. It did not include `gateway.auth.token`, `gateway.auth.password`, `gateway.remote.token`, or `gateway.remote.password`. When the status command loaded the config, it resolved only the listed secret targets. Gateway auth SecretRef objects remained unresolved.

The embedded security audit then called `resolveGatewayAuth()` with the unresolved config. `resolveGatewayAuth` saw a SecretRef object (not a string) for the token field, determined no auth was configured, and emitted the false `gateway.http.no_auth` finding.

The separate `STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS` array already included all four gateway auth paths, which is why `openclaw security audit --deep` worked correctly.

## Fix

Add the four gateway auth target IDs to `STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS` so the status command resolves gateway auth SecretRefs before the audit evaluates them.

## Real behavior proof

- Behavior addressed: `status --deep` falsely reports `gateway.auth.mode="none"` when token auth is configured via SecretRef, because `STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS` did not include the four gateway auth secret paths that `STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS` already listed.
- Real environment tested: macOS 15.4.1, Node 26.0.0, OpenClaw source checkout on branch `fix/status-deep-gateway-auth-secret-targets`.
- Exact steps or command run after this patch:

```bash
node -e "
const fs = require('node:fs');
const source = fs.readFileSync('src/cli/command-secret-targets.ts', 'utf8');
const statusMatch = source.match(/STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS[^=]*=\s*\[([\s\S]*?)\]\s*as/);
const auditMatch = source.match(/STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS[^=]*=\s*\[([\s\S]*?)\]\s*as/);
function extractIds(block) { return [...block.matchAll(/[\x22]([^\x22]+)[\x22]/g)].map(m => m[1]); }
const statusIds = extractIds(statusMatch[1]);
const auditIds = extractIds(auditMatch[1]);
console.log('STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS (' + statusIds.length + ' entries):');
statusIds.forEach(id => console.log('  ' + id));
console.log('');
console.log('STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS (' + auditIds.length + ' entries):');
auditIds.forEach(id => console.log('  ' + id));
console.log('');
const gatewayAuditIds = auditIds.filter(id => id.startsWith('gateway.'));
const missing = gatewayAuditIds.filter(id => !statusIds.includes(id));
console.log('Gateway auth targets missing from status resolution:', missing.length === 0 ? 'none (all resolved before audit runs)' : missing);
"
```

- Evidence after fix: terminal output copied below from the patched source:

```console
$ node -e "<source extraction script above>"
STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS (6 entries):
  agents.defaults.memorySearch.remote.apiKey
  agents.list[].memorySearch.remote.apiKey
  gateway.auth.token
  gateway.auth.password
  gateway.remote.token
  gateway.remote.password

STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS (4 entries):
  gateway.auth.token
  gateway.auth.password
  gateway.remote.token
  gateway.remote.password

Gateway auth targets missing from status resolution: none (all resolved before audit runs)
```

The patched `STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS` now contains all four gateway auth paths that `STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS` has, so the status command resolves auth SecretRefs before the embedded security audit inspects them.

- Observed result after fix: Terminal output confirms all four gateway auth secret paths are now present in `STATIC_STATUS_TARGET_IDS`, achieving parity with `STATIC_SECURITY_AUDIT_TARGET_IDS`. The `status --deep` command will resolve gateway auth SecretRefs before the audit evaluates them, preventing the false `gateway.http.no_auth` finding.
- What was not tested: Live `openclaw status --deep` with a running gateway configured with SecretRef token auth (requires deployed gateway with secret provider).

Closes #87815
